---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import SectionBlock from '../../components/SectionBlock/SectionBlock.astro';
import Grid from '../../components/Grid/Grid.astro';
import Card from '../../components/Card/Card.astro';
import Badge from '../../components/Badge/Badge.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer/Footer.astro';
import CopyCommandBlock from '../../components/CopyCommandBlock/CopyCommandBlock';
import { getSkillsAlternateLinks } from '../../lib/i18n';

const lang = 'en';
const alternateLinks = getSkillsAlternateLinks();
const qualityGateCommand =
  'npx skills@latest add baltazarparra/ai-native-engineering --skill quality-gate --agent codex --global';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Skills for coding agents | AI-Native Engineering"
  description="Learn what agent skills are, why they matter, and install a quality gate skill with NPX."
  lang={lang}
  alternateLinks={alternateLinks}
>
  <main id="main-content" class="skills-page">
    <SectionBlock as="header" padding="xl">
      <Badge variant="blue">Skills</Badge>
      <h1 class="page-title">Skills for coding agents</h1>
      <p class="page-summary">
        A simple way to package processes, habits, and tiny checklists so your
        agents can repeat the work better.
      </p>
    </SectionBlock>

    <SectionBlock padding="lg" alt>
      <div class="intro-grid">
        <div class="section-copy">
          <h2>What is a skill?</h2>
          <p>
            A skill is a reusable instruction set for an agent. Think of it as a
            small operating guide: when a situation shows up, the agent loads
            that process and follows the steps.
          </p>
          <p>
            In practice, it is usually a folder with a <code>SKILL.md</code>
            file containing a name, a description, and the instructions the agent
            should follow.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="code-card" aria-label="Skill folder example">
          <pre><code>skills/
  quality-gate/
    SKILL.md</code></pre>
        </div>
      </div>
    </SectionBlock>

    <SectionBlock padding="lg">
      <div class="section-stack">
        <div class="section-copy">
          <h2>What is it for?</h2>
          <p class="section-lead">
            Skills work best when they package a small, clear, repeatable
            behavior.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="card-grid">
          <Grid columns={3} gap="lg" align="stretch">
            <Card title="Quality gates" accent="yellow">
              <p>
                Run lint, tests, build, or type checks before handing a code
                change back.
              </p>
            </Card>
            <Card title="PR review" accent="blue">
              <p>
                Review pull requests using the team's criteria, not just loose
                preferences.
              </p>
            </Card>
            <Card title="Handoff" accent="green">
              <p>
                Prepare a clear summary of what changed, risks, validation, and
                next steps.
              </p>
            </Card>
          </Grid>
        </div>
        <p class="after-grid">
          Start with the minimum: instructions, small examples, and validation
          criteria. If the skill grows, move details into supporting files
          inside the skill folder. That lets the agent load the basics first and
          pull in extra resources only when needed.
        </p>
      </div>
    </SectionBlock>

    <SectionBlock padding="lg" alt>
      <div class="section-stack">
        <div class="section-copy">
          <h2>How does a skill get activated?</h2>
          <p>
            A skill is not a hard guarantee. It is a capability the agent can
            use. Most of the time, the agent sees the skill name and
            description, decides whether it matches the task, and only then
            loads the full <code>SKILL.md</code>.
          </p>
          <p>
            That makes the description very important. It should say what the
            skill does and when to use it. If the trigger is vague, the agent
            may simply continue without using the skill.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="card-grid">
          <Grid columns={3} gap="lg" align="stretch">
            <Card title="Implicit" accent="yellow">
              <p>
                The agent chooses the skill when the task appears to match its
                description.
              </p>
            </Card>
            <Card title="Explicit" accent="blue">
              <p>
                You call the skill by name, when the tool supports slash
                commands or direct invocation.
              </p>
            </Card>
            <Card title="Reinforced" accent="green">
              <p>
                A project rule reminds the agent to consider the skill at
                important moments.
              </p>
            </Card>
          </Grid>
        </div>
      </div>
    </SectionBlock>

    <SectionBlock padding="lg">
      <div class="section-stack">
        <div class="section-copy">
          <h2>Claude Code, Cursor, and the harness</h2>
          <p>
            Claude Code treats skills as capabilities the agent can discover.
            You can let Claude choose automatically, or invoke a skill directly
            with <code>/skill-name</code>. Claude Code also has frontmatter
            controls for manual-only or agent-only skills.
          </p>
          <p>
            Cursor also supports Agent Skills, but its strongest mental model
            still goes through Rules. Rules are persistent context for the
            Agent, and they can be always applied, attached by file patterns,
            requested by the agent, or called manually.
          </p>
          <p>
            In practice: if you want an implicit skill to fire more consistently
            in Cursor, pair it with a short project rule. The rule does not need
            to duplicate the whole skill. It only needs to remind the harness
            when to consider it.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="flow-card">
          <pre><code>---
description: Use the quality-gate skill after technical code tasks.
alwaysApply: true
---

After code edits, remind the agent to use the quality-gate skill
before handing the task back.</code></pre>
        </div>
      </div>
    </SectionBlock>

    <SectionBlock padding="lg" alt>
      <div class="section-stack">
        <div class="section-copy">
          <h2>Sharing skills</h2>
          <p>
            There are two useful paths for distributing skills: a simple
            <code>npx</code> command, or marketplaces/plugins when you need discovery,
            updates, and scale.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="share-options">
          <div class="share-option">
            <Badge variant="yellow">Repo + NPX</Badge>
            <h3>For getting started fast</h3>
            <p>
              Vercel created the
              <a href="https://www.npmjs.com/package/skills">skills</a> package: a
              CLI that installs, lists, updates, and removes skills for different
              coding agents. You do not publish your skill to npm. npm gives you the
              <code>skills</code> tool; your skill still lives on GitHub.
            </p>
            <div class="flow-card">
              <pre><code>npx runs the "skills" CLI
skills reads the GitHub repo
skills looks for SKILL.md files
skills installs the skill into the agent</code></pre>
            </div>
            <p>
              The CLI accepts <code>owner/repo</code>, a full GitHub URL, a
              direct path to a skill, GitLab, any git URL, and even a local
              folder while you are testing.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="share-option">
            <Badge variant="blue">Marketplaces</Badge>
            <h3>For distributing at scale</h3>
            <p>
              Claude Code also has
              <a href="https://code.claude.com/docs/en/plugins">plugins</a> and
              <a href="https://code.claude.com/docs/en/discover-plugins">
                marketplaces
              </a>. A plugin can bundle skills, agents, hooks, MCP servers, and
              other integrations.
            </p>
            <p>
              The practical difference:
              <strong>skills are the content</strong>;
              <strong>plugins are a distribution format</strong>. Anthropic's
              official marketplace is the
              <a href="https://claude.com/plugins">
                Claude plugins marketplace
              </a>, and Anthropic also documents how to
              <a href="https://code.claude.com/docs/en/plugin-marketplaces">
                create your own marketplace
              </a>.
            </p>
            <p>
              That does not automatically install anything into Cursor. For
              Cursor, see the
              <a href="https://cursor.com/marketplace">Cursor Marketplace</a> or use
              an installation path Cursor can discover. The
              <code>SKILL.md</code> format helps reuse, but each harness decides how
              to discover and apply the skill.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </SectionBlock>

    <SectionBlock padding="xl" id="ready-skills">
      <div class="section-stack">
        <div class="section-copy">
          <Badge variant="coral">Copy and paste</Badge>
          <h2 class="section-title">Ready-to-use skills</h2>
          <p class="section-lead">
            Starting small: one skill that reminds the agent to validate the
            project before handing code back.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="skill-card">
          <div class="skill-copy">
            <div>
              <h3>quality-gate</h3>
              <p>
                At the end of a technical task, the agent should find and run
                the best quality gate available: lint, tests, type check, build,
                or formatting.
              </p>
            </div>
            <CopyCommandBlock
              client:visible
              lang={lang}
              command={qualityGateCommand}
            />
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </SectionBlock>

    <SectionBlock padding="lg" alt>
      <div class="section-stack">
        <h2>References</h2>
        <ul class="reference-list">
          <li>
            <a
              href="https://help.openai.com/en/articles/20001066-skills-in-chatgpt"
            >
              OpenAI: Skills in ChatGPT
            </a>
          </li>
          <li>
            <a href="https://openai.com/index/introducing-the-codex-app/">
              OpenAI: Introducing the Codex app
            </a>
          </li>
          <li>
            <a href="https://claude.com/blog/skills-explained">
              Anthropic: Skills explained
            </a>
          </li>
          <li>
            <a href="https://code.claude.com/docs/en/skills">
              Claude Code: Extend Claude with skills
            </a>
          </li>
          <li>
            <a href="https://code.claude.com/docs/en/discover-plugins">
              Claude Code: Discover and install plugins
            </a>
          </li>
          <li>
            <a href="https://code.claude.com/docs/en/plugin-marketplaces">
              Claude Code: Create and distribute a plugin marketplace
            </a>
          </li>
          <li>
            <a href="https://docs.cursor.com/context/rules"> Cursor: Rules </a>
          </li>
          <li>
            <a href="https://cursor.com/changelog/2-4">
              Cursor: Skills support changelog
            </a>
          </li>
          <li>
            <a href="https://cursor.com/marketplace"> Cursor: Marketplace </a>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </SectionBlock>

    <Footer lang={lang} />
  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-title {
    margin-top: var(--space-md);
    max-width: 16ch;
  }

  .page-summary,
  .section-lead {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
  }

  .page-summary {
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    margin-top: var(--space-md);
    max-width: 62ch;
  }

  .section-title {
    margin-top: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .section-stack {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .section-copy {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-md);
    max-width: 72ch;
  }

  .section-copy h2,
  .section-copy p {
    margin: 0;
  }

  .section-lead {
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    max-width: 62ch;
  }

  .card-grid {
    margin-block: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .after-grid {
    margin: 0;
    max-width: 72ch;
  }

  .share-options {
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .share-option {
    border: var(--border-thick);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    background: var(--color-white);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-md);
    padding: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .share-option h3 {
    margin-top: var(--space-md);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .share-option p {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
    margin: 0;
    max-width: 72ch;
  }

  .share-option p + p {
    margin-top: var(--space-md);
  }

  .share-option .flow-card {
    margin-block: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .intro-grid {
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-xl);
    align-items: center;
  }

  .intro-grid h2 {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .intro-grid p,
  .skills-page section > p {
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
    max-width: 72ch;
  }

  .skills-page section > h2 + p {
    margin-top: var(--space-md);
  }

  .skills-page section > p + p {
    margin-top: var(--space-md);
  }

  .skills-page section > p + .flow-card,
  .flow-card + p {
    margin-top: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .code-card,
  .flow-card,
  .skill-card {
    border: var(--border-thick);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    background: var(--color-white);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-md);
  }

  .code-card,
  .flow-card {
    padding: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .code-card pre,
  .flow-card pre {
    margin: 0;
    overflow-x: auto;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
  }

  .skill-card {
    margin-top: var(--space-xl);
    padding: var(--space-lg);
    background: var(--color-bg-alt);
  }

  .skill-copy {
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .skill-copy h3 {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .skill-copy p {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
    margin: 0;
  }

  :global(.skills-page .card p) {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
  }

  .reference-list {
    padding-left: var(--space-lg);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
  }

  .reference-list li {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);
  }

  code {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
  }

  @media (min-width: 900px) {
    .intro-grid,
    .skill-copy,
    .share-options {
      grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1fr) minmax(320px, 0.9fr);
    }
  }
</style>
